sitar
The sitar is a plucked stringed instrument, originating from the Indian subcontinent, 
used in Hindustani classical music. 
The instrument is balanced between the player's left foot and right knee. 
The hands move freely without having to carry any of the instrument's weight.




tambura

The tanpura is a long-necked plucked string instrument, 
originating from India, found in various forms in Indian music. 
It does not play melody but rather supports and sustains the melody of another instrument or 
singer by providing a continuous harmonic bourdon or drone.

tabla
A tabla is a pair of twin hand drums from the Indian subcontinent. 
It is one of the main qawali instrument used by Sufi musicians. 


